text: Arizona's 28th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, situated in central Maricopa County. As of 2018 there are 57 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 135,025. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2019-2021 Legislative Session in the State Senate by Kate Brophy McGee (R) and in the House of Representatives by Kelli Butler (D) and Aaron Lieberman (D). ==See also== * List of Arizona Legislative Districts * Arizona State Legislature ==References== ==External links== * (Information based on U.S. Census Bureau's American Community Survey). * * Category:Maricopa County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 28th legislative district
